94.5	Socialist_realism	Socialist realism	Socialist realism is a style of realistic art which was developed in the Soviet Union and became a dominant style in other communist countries. Socialist realism is a teleologically-oriented style having its purpose the furtherance of the goals of socialism and communism. Although related, it should not be confused with social realism, a type of art that realistically depicts subjects of social concern. Unlike social realism, socialist realism often glorifies the roles of the poor.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Russia-Moscow-VDNH-3.jpg/220px-Russia-Moscow-VDNH-3.jpg
